title: Usage of top level domains for websites 2019
summary: This is a bar chart representing DNS names in the x axis and Share of global TLD in the y axis.
The Share of global TLD is appeared to be the highest at DNS names .com and lowest at DNS names .au.
DNS names .au has 36.92 times less Share of global TLD than DNS names .com which is the highest.
min_summary: This bar chart has 10 columns on the x axis representing DNS names, and Share of global TLD in each DNS names on the y axis.
The Share of global TLD is appeared to be the highest at DNS names .com and lowest at DNS names .au.

max_summary: This bar chart has 10 columns on the x axis representing DNS names, and Share of global TLD in each DNS names on the y axis.
The Share of global TLD is appeared to be the highest at DNS names .com and lowest at DNS names .au.
Second maximum Share of global TLD is found at DNS names .ru.
The difference of Share of global TLD between the highest and lowest DNS names is 46.7.
The DNS names .com has the highest Share of global TLD, followed by .ru, and .org. Down to the DNS names .au which is the lowest.
DNS names .au, and .jp have the same Share of global TLD.
The DNS names .au has 6.66 times less Share of global TLD than average.
The Share of global TLD is 72.1 if we add up values of all DNS namess.
